1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:50,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:50,656 --> 00:00:51,490
Hey.

3
00:00:52,783 --> 00:00:55,035
You're not treating Eui-ju like that
on purpose, are you?

4
00:00:55,828 --> 00:00:56,704
Like what?

5
00:00:57,413 --> 00:01:00,583
She told me she thinks
the essay and demerits are unfair.

6
00:01:01,292 --> 00:01:03,460
You're not doing that
because of the filming, right?

7
00:01:04,295 --> 00:01:05,129
Me?

8
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:06,964
You wouldn't, right?

9
00:01:07,798 --> 00:01:09,758
I'm pretty sure that was all
just a misunderstanding.

10
00:01:13,554 --> 00:01:14,805
I know she didn't film us.

11
00:01:18,809 --> 00:01:19,894
Then why are you doing it?

12
00:01:20,769 --> 00:01:23,147
Why are you being so strict with just her?

13
00:01:25,691 --> 00:01:27,109
I can't accept her…

14
00:01:28,819 --> 00:01:31,155
only getting four points in math.

15
00:01:37,328 --> 00:01:38,162
Have some breakfast.

16
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:41,957
I hear after-school classes don't happen
unless five kids sign up.

17
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:42,958
I only have four.

18
00:01:44,043 --> 00:01:45,836
I heard yesterday, Woo-su already has ten.

19
00:01:52,593 --> 00:01:54,386
Oh, you found your glasses.

20
00:01:54,470 --> 00:01:55,971
Took you long enough to notice.

21
00:01:56,055 --> 00:01:57,056
Dude!

22
00:01:57,139 --> 00:01:58,724
What's going on? You found them.

23
00:01:59,808 --> 00:02:02,186
-Where did you find them?
-Did someone see your flyer?

24
00:02:02,978 --> 00:02:04,063
How much did you give them?

25
00:02:05,064 --> 00:02:06,023
Why would I give any?

26
00:02:06,690 --> 00:02:07,650
Look at this punk.

27
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:09,234
The person didn't want a reward.

28
00:02:09,318 --> 00:02:10,361
-What?
-Why not?

29
00:02:11,487 --> 00:02:12,321
Who knows?

30
00:02:14,448 --> 00:02:15,783
What a lifesaver.

31
00:02:16,408 --> 00:02:17,785
You should bow to them, dude.

32
00:02:18,535 --> 00:02:21,705
You should express your gratitude
to bring more blessings back to yourself.

33
00:02:21,789 --> 00:02:23,707
Yeah, dude, it's the least you can do.

34
00:02:23,791 --> 00:02:26,293
-Otherwise you'll get pooped on again.
-Yeah, dude.

35
00:02:27,503 --> 00:02:29,171
CHAPTER 15:
BLINK TWICE IF YOU'RE HERE UNDER DURESS

36
00:02:29,254 --> 00:02:32,216
Is it just me or does your heart burst
every time Yoon picks up his pen?

37
00:02:32,299 --> 00:02:34,385
Even Si-on's breathing gets me
right in the feels.

38
00:02:34,468 --> 00:02:36,595
I wish I could be tied up
with that leather watch on Yoon's wrist.

39
00:02:36,679 --> 00:02:39,223
The way that Tae-ha looks at Yoon.
Is he for real?

40
00:02:50,359 --> 00:02:51,360
Hi.

41
00:02:51,443 --> 00:02:53,028
What's so funny?

42
00:02:53,112 --> 00:02:55,322
What? Well…

43
00:02:55,406 --> 00:02:56,865
The new thing I uploaded

44
00:02:57,491 --> 00:02:58,784
is causing quite a stir.

45
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:00,703
Really? Show me.

46
00:03:01,412 --> 00:03:02,871
I can't, it's embarrassing. Sorry.

47
00:03:04,456 --> 00:03:06,542
The way you're being
so secretive about it…

48
00:03:08,585 --> 00:03:09,712
Is it R-rated?

49
00:03:13,507 --> 00:03:15,384
No, don't be silly.

50
00:03:18,470 --> 00:03:21,598
It's not like BL, is it?

51
00:03:23,058 --> 00:03:24,309
BL?

52
00:03:24,393 --> 00:03:26,020
Yeah, you know,

53
00:03:26,103 --> 00:03:27,563
men liking other men.

54
00:03:29,773 --> 00:03:31,150
Oh, BL.

55
00:03:31,775 --> 00:03:33,402
I have heard of that.

56
00:03:35,612 --> 00:03:37,948
I don't get people
who like that kind of stuff.

57
00:03:40,492 --> 00:03:41,326
Of course.

58
00:03:42,369 --> 00:03:43,579
You're right.

59
00:03:44,204 --> 00:03:47,708
If it's a romance, why pair two guys
instead of a guy and a girl?

60
00:03:48,625 --> 00:03:49,960
What's so fun about that?

61
00:03:51,754 --> 00:03:52,921
Right.

62
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,758
Right.

63
00:03:57,634 --> 00:03:59,178
The weather's great, isn't it?

64
00:03:59,803 --> 00:04:00,637
Yeah.

65
00:04:01,555 --> 00:04:03,140
What's our first period?

66
00:04:09,396 --> 00:04:10,814
My dad always said…

67
00:04:13,025 --> 00:04:15,110
When faced with a difficult choice…

68
00:04:17,696 --> 00:04:18,822
Is that your application form?

69
00:04:19,615 --> 00:04:21,241
Finally got my fifth person.

70
00:04:21,325 --> 00:04:22,868
This is going to be an elite team.

71
00:04:23,452 --> 00:04:25,412
Let's do this,
rising star of the athletic world!

72
00:04:27,623 --> 00:04:28,874
Sorry, Mr. Jung.

73
00:04:34,213 --> 00:04:36,215
Taking the more difficult path…

74
00:04:37,091 --> 00:04:39,051
is the way to salvation.

75
00:04:42,179 --> 00:04:45,682
Mr. Jung, I really wanted to do
after-school PE.

76
00:04:46,725 --> 00:04:48,227
But something came up.

77
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:51,396
Blink twice if you're here under duress.

78
00:04:54,108 --> 00:04:55,567
She has a passion for math.

79
00:04:56,819 --> 00:04:59,154
She wants to get her score up
so I couldn't just say no.

80
00:05:00,739 --> 00:05:02,533
-Me?
-She should do what she's good at.

81
00:05:02,616 --> 00:05:04,701
Her long-distance running
is right up there.

82
00:05:05,202 --> 00:05:07,371
She obviously isn't an athletic type,
is she?

83
00:05:08,622 --> 00:05:10,332
Her face has got lazy written all over it.

84
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:12,000
Me?

85
00:05:12,084 --> 00:05:12,960
No, it doesn't.

86
00:05:13,043 --> 00:05:14,461
I'm really hard-working.

87
00:05:14,545 --> 00:05:15,420
How much do you sleep?

88
00:05:18,006 --> 00:05:18,841
Ten hours.

89
00:05:21,301 --> 00:05:22,928
As long as you focus when you're awake.

90
00:05:23,846 --> 00:05:24,888
What rank are your grades?

91
00:05:27,975 --> 00:05:28,976
Ninth.

92
00:05:35,607 --> 00:05:37,192
Listen to your homeroom teacher.

93
00:05:39,695 --> 00:05:40,571
But, sir.

94
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,615
They're not all nine.

95
00:05:56,420 --> 00:05:58,797
Today we're going to study the poem

96
00:05:58,881 --> 00:06:00,048
Invocation by Kim So-wol.

97
00:06:03,343 --> 00:06:05,888
INVOCATION

98
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,726
KIM SO-WOL

99
00:06:14,813 --> 00:06:16,690
Let me read it aloud first.

100
00:06:17,357 --> 00:06:18,984
"A name which was shattered into pieces."

101
00:06:26,116 --> 00:06:28,285
Why doesn't Dong-ju
use the present I gave him?

102
00:06:30,495 --> 00:06:32,331
He probably doesn't want to burden you.

103
00:06:33,332 --> 00:06:36,460
If he uses it, you might feel obliged
to get him something else.

104
00:06:37,169 --> 00:06:38,045
Do you think?

105
00:06:41,548 --> 00:06:44,092
I'm going to tell him I like him
as soon as I turn 20.

106
00:06:45,928 --> 00:06:48,388
You really think
you'll still like him until then?

107
00:06:48,472 --> 00:06:50,933
You've never even lasted 200 days before.

108
00:06:51,016 --> 00:06:52,643
This time it's different.

109
00:06:54,728 --> 00:06:56,688
I'm really curious.

110
00:06:56,772 --> 00:06:58,941
Why do you like Mr. Yoon?

111
00:06:59,024 --> 00:07:00,192
Like what specifically?

112
00:07:00,275 --> 00:07:02,319
Not his looks.
There must be something special.

113
00:07:03,111 --> 00:07:04,780
Dong-ju

114
00:07:05,364 --> 00:07:06,198
is different.

115
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,451
How is he different?

116
00:07:09,534 --> 00:07:11,620
Compared to all the other guys you dated.

117
00:07:20,254 --> 00:07:21,421
I feel sorry for him.

118
00:07:24,716 --> 00:07:25,550
What?

119
00:07:26,051 --> 00:07:27,302
I don't know.

120
00:07:27,386 --> 00:07:29,012
Just looking at his face

121
00:07:29,972 --> 00:07:30,847
makes me sad.

122
00:07:32,349 --> 00:07:33,976
It makes my heart ache.

123
00:07:39,481 --> 00:07:40,899
I guess.

124
00:07:40,983 --> 00:07:43,735
My mom said she married my dad
because she felt sorry for him.

125
00:07:43,819 --> 00:07:45,904
She also said never
to marry someone out of pity.

126
00:07:45,988 --> 00:07:48,323
That plenty of people
ruined their lives like that.

127
00:07:54,788 --> 00:07:56,957
But if you really like someone,

128
00:07:58,041 --> 00:07:59,710
I guess that's what it feels like.

129
00:08:00,294 --> 00:08:01,169
-Right?
-Yes.

130
00:08:04,298 --> 00:08:06,049
Feeling sorry for someone for no reason?

131
00:08:09,594 --> 00:08:11,722
I'm on cleaning duty again.

132
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:19,021
-Good afternoon.
-Good afternoon.

133
00:08:20,689 --> 00:08:21,648
Great work today.

134
00:08:22,232 --> 00:08:24,484
Just look at that face.

135
00:08:24,568 --> 00:08:26,236
Who's ever going to feel sorry for him?

136
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,363
Those on cleaning duty,
make sure you do it.

137
00:08:29,865 --> 00:08:32,409
No one, whatsoever.
For the rest of his life!

138
00:08:33,076 --> 00:08:33,952
Dismissed.

139
00:08:34,661 --> 00:08:36,747
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

140
00:08:39,499 --> 00:08:42,461
I can't say I'm surprised,
but he's a real freak.

141
00:08:42,544 --> 00:08:44,087
He hits you with demerits on a whim.

142
00:08:44,671 --> 00:08:45,964
And now after-school math too.

143
00:08:46,048 --> 00:08:47,632
He's the devil.

144
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:50,969
Let's do it together.

145
00:08:52,804 --> 00:08:55,265
I'd follow you to hell.

146
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,809
But after-school math? No.

147
00:08:58,769 --> 00:09:01,313
Punishing someone
with what they hate most.

148
00:09:01,396 --> 00:09:03,023
Honestly, it's genius. Right?

149
00:09:04,566 --> 00:09:05,609
Hey, girls.

150
00:09:05,692 --> 00:09:06,568
Do you have plans?

151
00:09:06,651 --> 00:09:08,320
-Not really.
-Nope.

152
00:09:08,403 --> 00:09:09,321
Why?

153
00:09:09,404 --> 00:09:12,324
I have detention cleaning
and then after-school class.

154
00:09:12,407 --> 00:09:13,408
Why do you ask?

155
00:09:15,285 --> 00:09:17,829
There's something I want to do
now that I'm in Korea.

156
00:09:17,913 --> 00:09:19,498
-What?
-What is it?

157
00:09:19,581 --> 00:09:20,957
What is it?

158
00:09:22,334 --> 00:09:24,628
CHAPTER 16:
MATH IS ABOUT PERSEVERANCE

159
00:09:39,351 --> 00:09:40,352
Mr. Jung.

160
00:09:40,894 --> 00:09:44,606
I guess all I can do
is gaze on you from afar.

161
00:09:46,274 --> 00:09:48,318
Is this unbearable pain in my heart

162
00:09:48,402 --> 00:09:50,070
because of a love that can never be?

163
00:09:50,987 --> 00:09:54,199
Why is fate so cruel to us?

164
00:09:54,908 --> 00:09:56,952
What are you doing here?
Do you have something to tell me?

165
00:09:58,662 --> 00:10:00,330
Mr. Ga forced you, right?

166
00:10:01,748 --> 00:10:03,208
Gosh.

167
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:04,126
No.

168
00:10:05,168 --> 00:10:07,087
Let me help you.

169
00:10:07,170 --> 00:10:08,338
Don't worry about it.

170
00:10:09,423 --> 00:10:10,340
There's no need.

171
00:10:12,342 --> 00:10:13,343
Oh, come on.

172
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:15,095
I said it's fine.

173
00:10:15,178 --> 00:10:16,179
Thanks.

174
00:10:20,142 --> 00:10:21,726
I'm not saying this for the sake of it.

175
00:10:21,810 --> 00:10:23,103
You're really talented.

176
00:10:25,522 --> 00:10:26,898
So feel free to ask me anything.

177
00:10:27,774 --> 00:10:29,443
If you need anything, just tell me.

178
00:10:30,485 --> 00:10:31,319
Okay.

179
00:10:36,074 --> 00:10:36,908
So…

180
00:10:37,868 --> 00:10:41,204
You competed in the singles luge

181
00:10:41,288 --> 00:10:45,417
until you were forced to retire
after fracturing your left shin.

182
00:10:47,085 --> 00:10:48,295
How did you know that?

183
00:10:49,171 --> 00:10:50,464
I read a news article about it.

184
00:10:51,923 --> 00:10:53,467
It doesn't affect my daily life.

185
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:57,429
But you were forced to retire after
finishing fourth at the Winter Games.

186
00:10:57,512 --> 00:10:59,139
You must have a lot of regrets.

187
00:11:00,599 --> 00:11:01,475
Are you asking

188
00:11:02,434 --> 00:11:03,894
if I regret not having won a medal?

189
00:11:09,149 --> 00:11:11,234
There's something
more important than that.

190
00:11:12,194 --> 00:11:14,863
As I watched the medalists
from below the podium,

191
00:11:15,363 --> 00:11:16,531
I realized something.

192
00:11:17,949 --> 00:11:21,328
Despite all the sweat I shed to compete
in the Games, they must have shed more.

193
00:11:23,580 --> 00:11:24,956
I thought I was going to die.

194
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,460
They must have felt the same, right?

195
00:11:36,301 --> 00:11:38,261
In that moment,
my placing no longer mattered.

196
00:11:40,347 --> 00:11:41,556
And above all,

197
00:11:45,936 --> 00:11:47,521
I'd kept my promise to myself.

198
00:11:50,690 --> 00:11:51,900
I never gave up.

199
00:11:53,026 --> 00:11:53,944
That's what counts.

200
00:11:57,906 --> 00:11:59,407
If I'd done after-school PE,

201
00:11:59,491 --> 00:12:02,369
we could have talked all the time
and gotten close.

202
00:12:03,828 --> 00:12:05,330
If it wasn't for Mr. Ga…

203
00:12:13,672 --> 00:12:15,090
-Hello?
-Where are you?

204
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:19,553
Come to my office
and get the printouts for the class.

205
00:12:21,304 --> 00:12:22,722
Can't you get someone else to do it?

206
00:12:22,806 --> 00:12:23,974
I'm sure Ha-su would love to.

207
00:12:24,057 --> 00:12:25,767
But you're the TA
for this after-school class.

208
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:26,726
Since when?

209
00:12:26,810 --> 00:12:27,811
You've got three minutes.

210
00:12:31,690 --> 00:12:33,525
Mr. Jung, I need to go.

211
00:12:33,608 --> 00:12:35,026
-You're leaving?
-Yes.

212
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:36,278
Goodbye.

213
00:12:43,785 --> 00:12:45,662
She's top of class one.

214
00:12:46,454 --> 00:12:48,623
And she's top of class three.

215
00:12:49,291 --> 00:12:51,585
This class is the best of the best.

216
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:53,837
I don't belong here at all.

217
00:13:06,891 --> 00:13:08,310
Are you here to bring us these?

218
00:13:12,147 --> 00:13:14,649
No, I'm taking this class too.

219
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:16,568
You? Why?

220
00:13:18,820 --> 00:13:20,196
Mr. Ga told me I should.

221
00:13:21,323 --> 00:13:22,198
Mr. Ga?

222
00:13:22,991 --> 00:13:25,076
It's probably so we don't waste our time.

223
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:27,037
It's better she does all that.

224
00:13:28,538 --> 00:13:29,914
Do you think?

225
00:13:29,998 --> 00:13:30,874
I guess.

226
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:34,002
She got four points
in the September mock exam.

227
00:13:36,630 --> 00:13:37,797
Four points?

228
00:14:28,765 --> 00:14:29,599
Where are you going?

229
00:14:30,183 --> 00:14:31,017
Mr. Ga.

230
00:14:31,643 --> 00:14:33,645
Can't you just let me go?

231
00:14:33,728 --> 00:14:37,023
I'm too bad at math to be in this class.

232
00:14:37,107 --> 00:14:40,360
My old tutor and my cousin both told me

233
00:14:40,443 --> 00:14:42,737
I don't have a head for math.
I think they were right.

234
00:14:42,821 --> 00:14:46,783
I'm totally hopeless with numbers.

235
00:14:47,367 --> 00:14:48,785
Unlike subjects you can memorize,

236
00:14:48,868 --> 00:14:51,413
more effort doesn't always mean
better scores.

237
00:14:53,248 --> 00:14:54,499
Those four points.

238
00:14:54,582 --> 00:14:56,251
How did you get them? Did you just guess?

239
00:14:57,127 --> 00:14:58,461
No, I solved them.

240
00:15:18,732 --> 00:15:19,733
There you go!

241
00:15:19,816 --> 00:15:21,985
When Gauss estimated the number of primes,

242
00:15:22,068 --> 00:15:25,196
he spent years manually calculating
every single prime up to three million.

243
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,282
Math is about perseverance,
and you have it in spades.

244
00:15:27,365 --> 00:15:29,534
So get back in there.

245
00:15:29,617 --> 00:15:30,660
But…

246
00:15:31,578 --> 00:15:33,663
Since angle CFA

247
00:15:34,247 --> 00:15:36,499
is equal to angle CAF,

248
00:15:37,417 --> 00:15:41,254
AC equals CF, which is 14.

249
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:43,757
Now try and solve it.

250
00:15:59,939 --> 00:16:02,817
What the heck?
Why is she putting lip tint on?

251
00:16:03,401 --> 00:16:04,778
And during class at that.

252
00:16:05,612 --> 00:16:06,571
No way!

253
00:16:08,364 --> 00:16:09,365
Wow!

254
00:16:10,074 --> 00:16:11,785
I know they say
birds of a feather and all.

255
00:16:11,868 --> 00:16:14,788
Does she like Mr. Ga? Amazing!

256
00:16:23,797 --> 00:16:25,673
When am I going to write episode three?

257
00:16:37,727 --> 00:16:38,937
Yeo Eui-ju!

258
00:16:39,020 --> 00:16:39,854
Yes, sir!

259
00:16:40,647 --> 00:16:41,606
Yes.

260
00:16:42,190 --> 00:16:43,691
Aren't you going to write episode three?

261
00:16:45,193 --> 00:16:46,820
Episode three?

262
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,154
Yes.

263
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:49,864
Explain how it goes.

264
00:16:58,498 --> 00:17:01,167
Readers will probably expect

265
00:17:01,251 --> 00:17:05,922
Yoon to pay back the ten million won
in episode three,

266
00:17:07,549 --> 00:17:10,468
but the highlight of episode three
is the swoon-inducing scene

267
00:17:10,552 --> 00:17:12,262
between Si-on and Yoon.

268
00:17:12,345 --> 00:17:14,556
They're studying together
at Si-on's place,

269
00:17:15,139 --> 00:17:16,432
when Si-on says to Yoon,

270
00:17:17,559 --> 00:17:20,144
"You're really bad."

271
00:17:20,228 --> 00:17:22,564
"You keep making me think bad thoughts."

272
00:17:22,647 --> 00:17:23,648
Yoon replies,

273
00:17:24,232 --> 00:17:25,900
"Stop messing around."

274
00:17:25,984 --> 00:17:27,402
To which Si-on responds,

275
00:17:27,485 --> 00:17:29,821
"Do I look like I'm joking?"

276
00:17:29,904 --> 00:17:33,324
"I've never once joked with you!"

277
00:17:33,408 --> 00:17:35,368
…joked with you.

278
00:17:57,640 --> 00:18:00,685
Do the problems we covered in class today
and hand them in tomorrow.

279
00:18:01,519 --> 00:18:03,146
By tomorrow? How am I supposed…

280
00:18:07,609 --> 00:18:09,068
Damn it.

281
00:18:10,361 --> 00:18:14,824
CHAPTER 17:
JMT! (JUST A MARVELOUS TEACHER)

282
00:18:14,908 --> 00:18:17,160
There's something I want to do
now that I'm in Korea!

283
00:18:17,243 --> 00:18:19,370
GUESTHOUSE

284
00:18:19,454 --> 00:18:21,998
A pajama party!

285
00:18:28,755 --> 00:18:30,465
-Eui-ju!
-It's Eui-ju!

286
00:18:30,548 --> 00:18:31,674
Where have you been?

287
00:18:31,758 --> 00:18:33,343
Why are you so late?

288
00:18:33,426 --> 00:18:36,387
Is this the famous shaman's place?

289
00:18:36,471 --> 00:18:37,680
Be seated.

290
00:18:37,764 --> 00:18:39,349
How did you come to be here?

291
00:18:39,432 --> 00:18:41,309
-Is your name Yeo Eui-ju?
-Verily.

292
00:18:41,392 --> 00:18:42,393
Hello.

293
00:18:42,477 --> 00:18:43,937
-What took you so long?
-You're so late!

294
00:18:44,729 --> 00:18:46,731
Got you a present. Welcome!

295
00:18:46,814 --> 00:18:48,775
Oh, Eui-ju.

296
00:18:48,858 --> 00:18:49,859
So sweet!

297
00:18:49,943 --> 00:18:51,152
That's so cute!

298
00:18:51,235 --> 00:18:52,695
-Where's mine?
-It's really cute.

299
00:18:52,779 --> 00:18:54,697
-It's really cute.
-Thank you.

300
00:18:55,281 --> 00:18:56,658
Wow, you ate all this?

301
00:18:56,741 --> 00:18:58,034
-It's nothing.
-I'm bursting.

302
00:18:58,117 --> 00:18:59,827
Thus doth Kim Dan-ji proclaim.

303
00:18:59,911 --> 00:19:02,497
Eat like there's no tomorrow!

304
00:19:03,289 --> 00:19:04,374
I'm so full.

305
00:19:04,999 --> 00:19:06,209
What is that?

306
00:19:06,292 --> 00:19:07,794
Yeah! Now it's a party.

307
00:19:07,877 --> 00:19:09,087
-That's a must.
-Of course!

308
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:11,422
Let me just make some space.

309
00:19:11,506 --> 00:19:13,633
-We always have a space for dessert!
-Rice cake sticks!

310
00:19:13,716 --> 00:19:14,634
Sweet potato.

311
00:19:14,717 --> 00:19:16,135
Let's go to the kitchen.

312
00:19:16,219 --> 00:19:17,095
Go to the kitchen!

313
00:19:17,178 --> 00:19:18,846
Let's go!

314
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:20,932
Put this on before we go.

315
00:19:21,015 --> 00:19:21,849
This?

316
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:24,519
Jenny, well done.

317
00:19:24,602 --> 00:19:26,562
Put them like this.

318
00:19:29,774 --> 00:19:30,984
And roast them.

319
00:19:32,443 --> 00:19:35,530
I'll show you the proper taste of Korea.

320
00:19:35,613 --> 00:19:37,615
I can't wait.

321
00:19:37,699 --> 00:19:39,784
Looks good, right?

322
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:40,785
Yes.

323
00:19:41,953 --> 00:19:44,163
-It's really warm.
-It is, right?

324
00:19:46,874 --> 00:19:48,835
What? Do you need something?

325
00:19:49,961 --> 00:19:50,878
So…

326
00:19:53,214 --> 00:19:55,550
Hey, Jenny, by any chance,

327
00:19:57,260 --> 00:19:59,887
do you know A Night in Paris?

328
00:19:59,971 --> 00:20:01,222
A NIGHT IN PARIS

329
00:20:01,973 --> 00:20:04,100
You know that novel?

330
00:20:05,601 --> 00:20:08,312
Yeah, it used to be my favorite.

331
00:20:08,396 --> 00:20:13,276
The female protagonist, Isabelle,
meets her Brazilian boyfriend in Paris.

332
00:20:13,359 --> 00:20:15,069
At the Louvre.

333
00:20:15,153 --> 00:20:17,697
I did a double take
when I saw your messenger username.

334
00:20:17,780 --> 00:20:20,283
But what you told us about
how he asked you out was the same.

335
00:20:23,161 --> 00:20:25,580
So you knew all along.

336
00:20:25,663 --> 00:20:27,040
That I lied.

337
00:20:27,915 --> 00:20:29,584
Don't worry about it.

338
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:31,836
Everyone wants to be the star
of their own novel.

339
00:20:31,919 --> 00:20:34,881
I just assumed you really like that novel.

340
00:20:36,215 --> 00:20:37,508
I don't really have a boyfriend.

341
00:20:38,092 --> 00:20:40,553
Everything I know about love
I learned from books.

342
00:20:42,263 --> 00:20:43,639
It's fine.

343
00:20:43,723 --> 00:20:45,099
It's no big deal.

344
00:20:45,683 --> 00:20:46,726
-Really?
-Yeah.

345
00:20:48,394 --> 00:20:50,271
I read it in translation first.

346
00:20:50,354 --> 00:20:52,899
And I really wanted to read the original.

347
00:20:52,982 --> 00:20:55,234
That's why I started learning Korean.

348
00:20:57,111 --> 00:21:00,573
You speak Korean this well
after learning from a novel?

349
00:21:01,783 --> 00:21:04,452
I read it so often
I practically memorized it.

350
00:21:07,121 --> 00:21:09,624
Do you like to read romance novels too?

351
00:21:09,707 --> 00:21:11,959
Well, you know.

352
00:21:12,585 --> 00:21:15,213
I started off by reading modern romances.

353
00:21:15,296 --> 00:21:18,925
Then I switched
to foreign romantic fantasy.

354
00:21:19,008 --> 00:21:20,301
And after that…

355
00:21:23,012 --> 00:21:24,097
And after that?

356
00:21:26,349 --> 00:21:27,892
Anyhow.

357
00:21:27,975 --> 00:21:30,812
Modern romance is the most mainstream.

358
00:21:32,855 --> 00:21:33,940
Right.

359
00:21:34,023 --> 00:21:37,735
I fell in love with Korea
after reading Korean romance web novels.

360
00:21:38,319 --> 00:21:40,404
Oh, I see.

361
00:21:41,280 --> 00:21:43,741
Which other novels did you enjoy?

362
00:21:45,952 --> 00:21:48,830
Fifty Shades of Mr. CEO.
Have you heard of it?

363
00:21:48,913 --> 00:21:50,748
-Of course! Have you read it?
-Yes!

364
00:21:51,415 --> 00:21:52,583
Did you read it too?

365
00:21:55,461 --> 00:21:56,337
-You did a great job.
-Looking good.

366
00:21:56,921 --> 00:21:59,048
-Hey, this rice cake is amazing.
-Stop it.

367
00:21:59,132 --> 00:22:00,383
You cooked these perfectly.

368
00:22:00,466 --> 00:22:02,260
Right? Have a bite.

369
00:22:02,885 --> 00:22:04,303
Oh, not yet.

370
00:22:04,387 --> 00:22:06,305
-Yeah, you need to add some kimchi.
-Sweet potatoes…

371
00:22:06,389 --> 00:22:08,724
-Kimchi?
-Yes, put it on top…

372
00:22:13,855 --> 00:22:15,231
How is it?

373
00:22:15,314 --> 00:22:16,899
-Wow!
-Isn't it great?

374
00:22:16,983 --> 00:22:18,067
Just marvelously tasty!

375
00:22:20,486 --> 00:22:22,071
You've got something on your face.

376
00:22:22,155 --> 00:22:24,282
-You've got something here as well.
-Come here.

377
00:22:24,365 --> 00:22:25,491
-Hey!
-No, I don't.

378
00:22:25,575 --> 00:22:27,160
Jenny, too.

379
00:22:27,243 --> 00:22:29,203
Hey!

380
00:22:30,371 --> 00:22:31,581
-With some grain syrup.
-Honey.

381
00:22:31,664 --> 00:22:33,207
-It's honey.
-Try it.

382
00:22:33,291 --> 00:22:34,208
It's good, right?

383
00:22:34,292 --> 00:22:35,585
-Do you like it?
-Isn't it great?

384
00:22:35,668 --> 00:22:37,670
This is just marvelously tasty too!

385
00:22:40,548 --> 00:22:42,008
This is nice.

386
00:22:42,091 --> 00:22:43,843
Man, I'm so full.

387
00:22:45,011 --> 00:22:46,804
Look at all those stars.

388
00:22:48,931 --> 00:22:51,684
There are so many of us, right?

389
00:22:53,060 --> 00:22:55,146
Like Mr. Ga said.

390
00:22:55,229 --> 00:22:57,273
We're all stars in the universe.

391
00:22:59,358 --> 00:23:02,904
When he says things like that,
doesn't he sound like the Little Prince?

392
00:23:03,613 --> 00:23:05,239
Know what I mean?

393
00:23:05,323 --> 00:23:08,326
Somewhere in the sky,
one of those shining stars belongs to me.

394
00:23:08,951 --> 00:23:10,995
And that star is speaking to me.

395
00:23:11,078 --> 00:23:12,330
Have you done your homework?

396
00:23:13,539 --> 00:23:15,499
-No!
-What is it?

397
00:23:18,252 --> 00:23:20,171
My math homework!

398
00:23:20,796 --> 00:23:22,757
No, my math homework.

399
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:25,968
I couldn't even hang out properly
because of after-school math.

400
00:23:26,052 --> 00:23:27,511
When am I supposed to do my homework?

401
00:23:27,595 --> 00:23:29,180
I hate it.

402
00:23:29,263 --> 00:23:30,890
I hate it so much.

403
00:23:30,973 --> 00:23:33,226
Aren't you going to get more demerits
if you don't do it?

404
00:23:33,309 --> 00:23:35,645
-She's right.
-Whatever.

405
00:23:36,687 --> 00:23:37,855
What are you going to do?

406
00:23:37,939 --> 00:23:39,190
No idea.

407
00:23:39,273 --> 00:23:41,692
No idea, I don't care!

408
00:23:41,776 --> 00:23:44,946
Eui-ju, you've become gutsy.

409
00:23:45,029 --> 00:23:47,031
Did you see his face
when she faked being sick?

410
00:23:47,114 --> 00:23:48,658
-I remember.
-I know.

411
00:23:48,741 --> 00:23:50,409
He gave her a look of death.

412
00:23:50,868 --> 00:23:56,332
CHAPTER 18:
STRANGELY FAMILIAR, ALMOST MATHEMATICAL

413
00:24:05,132 --> 00:24:06,425
Mr. Ga.

414
00:24:08,052 --> 00:24:10,721
I couldn't do the homework.

415
00:24:11,264 --> 00:24:13,224
Can I just write out the solutions
ten times each?

416
00:24:13,307 --> 00:24:14,558
Did you even try?

417
00:24:17,645 --> 00:24:19,939
Keep trying until you can solve
at least one by yourself.

418
00:24:20,022 --> 00:24:21,691
Like you did on the mock exam.

419
00:24:22,817 --> 00:24:25,361
That only works sometimes.

420
00:24:25,444 --> 00:24:26,696
This isn't one of those times.

421
00:24:28,531 --> 00:24:29,365
Yeo Eui-ju.

422
00:24:30,825 --> 00:24:31,742
Yes, sir?

423
00:24:31,826 --> 00:24:33,619
What did I say math was on my first day?

424
00:24:40,293 --> 00:24:41,377
The universe.

425
00:24:44,463 --> 00:24:45,423
Euclid?

426
00:24:45,506 --> 00:24:46,924
In here, not during class.

427
00:24:56,475 --> 00:24:58,227
I said it's a subject
that requires thought.

428
00:25:00,229 --> 00:25:01,314
Yes, sir.

429
00:25:01,397 --> 00:25:03,899
You probably weren't paying attention.
Nor are you now.

430
00:25:08,154 --> 00:25:10,948
I thought solving one problem
would make you think.

431
00:25:12,992 --> 00:25:15,286
I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause.

432
00:25:18,581 --> 00:25:19,540
I'm very disappointed.

433
00:25:33,596 --> 00:25:34,889
I'm sorry.

434
00:25:48,235 --> 00:25:50,780
What on earth was he expecting of me
to be so disappointed?

435
00:25:52,782 --> 00:25:54,367
He even made me feel sorry for him.

436
00:25:58,746 --> 00:26:00,623
Still at least,
I got some dialogue out of it.

437
00:26:07,963 --> 00:26:10,466
So, how did he pay back the ten million?

438
00:26:10,549 --> 00:26:12,676
You keeping the rest
of this juicy story to yourself?

439
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:13,928
Did she faint while writing?

440
00:26:14,011 --> 00:26:15,096
Give me my episode three!

441
00:26:15,179 --> 00:26:17,556
Episode three!

442
00:26:18,766 --> 00:26:20,810
The lines from Mr. Ga goes…

443
00:26:23,062 --> 00:26:24,772
I DIDN'T REALIZE YOU WERE SUCH…

444
00:26:26,399 --> 00:26:30,778
I'M VERY DISAPPOINTED, YOON

445
00:26:32,238 --> 00:26:34,490
I didn't realize
you were such a lost cause.

446
00:26:35,408 --> 00:26:37,201
I'm very disappointed, Yoon.

447
00:26:39,829 --> 00:26:40,830
Why?

448
00:26:45,543 --> 00:26:47,670
How can you read at a time like this?

449
00:26:51,173 --> 00:26:52,425
Stop messing around.

450
00:26:53,717 --> 00:26:55,845
Is Tae-ha gonna be waiting
outside your house again?

451
00:26:57,179 --> 00:26:58,264
YOON'S PAUSE INCENSES SI-ON

452
00:26:58,347 --> 00:26:59,306
I don't know.

453
00:27:00,307 --> 00:27:01,600
You're really bad.

454
00:27:04,770 --> 00:27:06,355
You keep making me think bad thoughts.

455
00:27:07,940 --> 00:27:10,651
I love it when you look at me, lying down.

456
00:27:10,734 --> 00:27:12,570
It makes me want to smush
my lips against yours.

457
00:27:12,653 --> 00:27:14,613
Until you can't breathe.

458
00:27:14,697 --> 00:27:16,615
SI-ON PRESSED AGAINST YOON,
HIS BREATHING RAGGED

459
00:27:29,295 --> 00:27:31,881
Now that's a proper cliffhanger.

460
00:27:31,964 --> 00:27:34,550
There's no way
you can skip the next episode.

461
00:27:49,231 --> 00:27:50,941
That smell

462
00:27:51,025 --> 00:27:53,903
isn't one I'm used to in the library.

463
00:27:56,238 --> 00:27:58,741
And yet, it's strangely familiar.
How should I put it…

464
00:27:58,824 --> 00:28:02,328
Like a skincare lotion
that a jerk would use.

465
00:28:03,162 --> 00:28:05,289
Almost…

466
00:28:06,540 --> 00:28:08,751
mathematical?

467
00:28:15,966 --> 00:28:17,635
I must be mistaken.

468
00:28:17,718 --> 00:28:19,929
Keep calm, Eui-ju.

469
00:28:21,514 --> 00:28:23,265
It's probably nothing.

470
00:28:24,391 --> 00:28:27,895
No, it's nothing.

471
00:28:47,248 --> 00:28:48,165
Move!

472
00:28:48,791 --> 00:28:50,000
Stay right there, Yeo Eui-ju!

473
00:28:51,669 --> 00:28:52,628
I mean,

474
00:28:55,130 --> 00:28:55,965
I.

475
00:28:57,341 --> 00:28:58,175
Muk.

476
00:30:15,919 --> 00:30:17,921
Subtitle: Paul Carver
